This was awesome!!! I used bowtie instead of ziti and when it was all combined put it in a 13 x 9 pan and topped it with grated swiss cheese (similar to a Reuben!) and baked it for about 20 minutes. It would be good to chop up the sausage a little more so that you get a piece in every bite! I used more cayanne than a pinch! I will definitely make this again and everyone I shared it with loved it. It's a nice change from what I usually make: Turkey Kilbasa with sauerkraut and a side of mashed potatoes. Plus, SO doesn't really love sauerkraut like I do, but he loved this! This is really wonderful!!!

